</div>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-idp10424992">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idm113996224">
<p id="fs-idm118172320">What is [H<sub>3</sub>O<sup>+</sup>] in a solution of 0.25 <em data-effect="italics">M</em> CH<sub>3</sub>CO<sub>2</sub>H and 0.030 <em data-effect="italics">M</em> NaCH<sub>3</sub>CO<sub>2</sub>?<span data-type="newline"><br/></span>
<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>CH</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mtext>CO</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msub><mtext>H</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>q</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub><mtext>O</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>l</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><mo stretchy="false">&#8652;</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mtext>O</mtext><mtext>+</mtext></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>q</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mtext>CH</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mtext>CO</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mtext>&#8722;</mtext></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>q</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mspace width="5em"/><msub><mi>K</mi><mtext>a</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1.8</mn><mspace width="0.2em"/><mo>&#215;</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>&#8722;5</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>CH</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mtext>CO</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msub><mtext>H</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>q</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>2</mn></msub><mtext>O</mtext><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>l</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><mo stretchy="false">&#8652;</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><msub><mtext>H</mtext><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mtext>O</mtext><mtext>+</mtext></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>q</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mtext>CH</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mtext>CO</mtext></mrow><mn>2</mn></msub><msup><mrow/><mtext>&#8722;</mtext></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>q</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mspace width="5em"/><msub><mi>K</mi><mtext>a</mtext></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1.8</mn><mspace width="0.2em"/><mo>&#215;</mo><mspace width="0.2em"/><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>&#8722;5</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-idm1744464">
<p id="fs-idm115330864">[H<sub>3</sub>O<sup>+</sup>] = 1.5 <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mo>&#215;</mo></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mo>&#215;</mo></annotation-xml></semantics></math> 10<sup>&#8722;4</sup> <em data-effect="italics">M</em></p>
</div>
</div>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-idm163403536">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idm57321696">
<p id="fs-idm63656480">What is [H<sub>3</sub>O<sup>+</sup>] in a solution of 0.075 <em data-effect="italics">M</em> HNO<sub>2</sub> and 0.030 <em data-effect="italics">M</em> NaNO<sub>2</sub>?<span data-type="newline"><br/></span>
